				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While the thought of this thing attacking people, coupled with its sound effect, makes for a pretty silly image, this is nowheres near as hilarious or endearing as similar SCPs, like <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2258">SCP-2258</a> or <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3092">SCP-3092</a>. I think too much goes into detailing its relocation effect, which really does not contribute to the sillier elements, and really dulls down what could have been more entertaining.</p> <p>Minor note, I would consider swapping the 2nd and 3rd paragraphs of the description, since the 3rd describes relocation, while the 2nd details its subsequent activity.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
