					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5700926#post-3761710</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5700926/scp-3832#post-3761710</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 07 Apr 2018 05:27:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Veiedhimaedhr</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3737554</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That's a good question. And it depends a lot on head canon(whether you'll accept what I'm about to say) and on whether you're just letting your tears fall on it or if you're pressing your face into it and sobbing. For the former, I'd say that the pillow would get a bit wet and eventually poof on out of there. For the latter&#8230;well it leaves faster when being actively restrained. But in the spirit of what this skip represents, I'll say it won't mind being cried into for just a little bit longer. ❤</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
